physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Extraoral examination revealed correct proportion of facial thirds, slightly deficient zygomatic projection, right and left ear shells lateralization, prominent ears, an extra tubercle at the top of the left ear, left converging right eye strabismus, bilateral epicantal folds, and a broad nasal bridge. Lateral analysis showed a straight profile, suitable chin-neckline, and a closed nasolabial angle. The patient has bilateral ectrodactyly in hands and feet. The right hand is missing the third finger entirely. The left hand has all fingers but shows malformation of the distal phalanges of fingers three and four. Both feet are missing fingers two, three, and four completely.
